content.description: Head up a line of discontinuous cracks on the center of the face. A brief section of steeper jamming marks the crux.
content.protection: Pro to 2.5 inches. Can anchor off a large boulder on top.
content.location: 25 ft to the right of TIGE. Start on top of a boulder.

content.description:
This climbs the right-most dike on the face to the right of "James Brown". I'm not sure where the actual start is, because there are a few ways to this dike. What seems to be the most direct start is to climb a short corner, with a bush at the base or the blunt arete to the right, then up face passing three horizontal cracks to the base of the dike system. follow this to the top passing one bolt.

Boulders on top can be slung for anchors.
content.protection: Pro to 2" or 2.5", I don't remember. A couple of the horizontals are about the same size, so you may want to double up from 1"-2". Bring a 30' sling, if you want to set up a TR.

content.description:
This fun, easy route climbs a wide crack/corner on the left side of the west face.

Start from two boulders perched on a sloping ledge. Move up behind the larger boulder and up a wide crack to it's end, then move up and left to the main crack system. I step up into the wide crack on the left then stem over to the hand crack on the right, eventually moving into the hand crack and following it to the top.
Start at the right side of the dome and follow 5 bolts up the face.  The rock is a little crispy but there is some decent climbing and a "hole in the wall" just where you need it.
content.protection: 5 bolts.  Gear up to a #3 camalot between 4th & 5th bolt.  Build an anchor and walk off to the right.
content.location: Climbs up the face on the far right side of the dome.

climbs.name: Buster Brown
climbs.fa: Kevin Powell, Paula Chambers & Darrel Hensel, 1983

content.description: On the left side of the face, climb the right-leaning dike.
content.protection: Small to medium pro, fixed pin and a bolt.

climbs.name: Brown Sugar
climbs.fa: (TR) Bob Gaines, March 2000, FL: Bob Gaines, December 2003

content.description: The face between Tige and Buster Brown, following faint dikes. Well protected by 5 bolts and CDs to 2 inches. The crux is a bouldery sequence over the bulge at the second bolt (11+). The upper dike is 10b/c.
content.protection: 5 bolts, CDs to 2 inches. To rig a top rope, a long extendo rope (80 ft.) is handy. For the anchor: 3 to 4 inch CDs plus a huge block.
content.location: Descend by scrambling down to the north. (left as you face the cliff)
